Source: snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), dh-sequence-dkms
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Cirrus CS8409/CS42L83 HDA codec driver for Apple iMac18,3
 DKMS module that adds Apple iMac18,3 (2017 27" 5K) audio support to the
 in-kernel Cirrus Logic CS8409 HDA codec driver. The CS8409 bridges to a
 CS42L83 companion DAC over I2C; this build adds the Apple quirk, GPIO/ASP2
 routing and 44.1kHz CS42L83 bring-up needed for the headphone path. It
 installs into updates/dkms so it overrides the stock in-tree module.
